config.userPrompt:
Write a 3-4 paragraph executive introduction for a contract comparison report with the following metadata:

- Base document: {{baseDocName}}
- Comparison documents: {{comparisonDocNames|join(', ')}}
- Number of comparison documents: {{comparisonFiles|length}}
- Total clause classifications across all comparisons: {{allClauses|length}}

## Clause Amendment Data
{{allClauses|string}}

The introduction should:
1. Identify the base document and each comparison document by name
2. Describe the scope and methodology (deterministic paragraph-level text comparison)
3. Analyze the clause amendment data to identify:
   - Which clause types were most frequently modified or negotiated across all comparison documents
   - The distribution of change types (Addition vs Deletion vs Modification vs Rewording)
   - Any patterns (e.g., certain clauses consistently modified across all versions)
4. Direct the reader to the detailed comparison that follows

Keep it under 250 words. Be specific about which clauses were most frequently amended.

